<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-11-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-11-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="260" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d260">
                            <head>[Telegram.—Translation.]</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-11-04"><hi rend="italic">November 4,
                                        1903</hi>.</date><lb/>(Received 10.30
                                p.m.)</dateline></opener>
                            <p rend="flushleft">To His Excellency the <hi rend="smallcaps">President
                                    of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington:</hi></p>
                            <p>The municipality of Panama is now (10 p.m.) holding a solemn session,
                                and joins in the movement of separation of the Isthmus of Panama
                                from the rest of Colombia. It hopes for recognition of our cause by
                                your Government.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Demetro S.
                                Brida.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>